WEBVTT

NOTE
English captions for "The Voice of Change"
This file provides synchronized captions for accessibility

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:08.000
Welcome to StoryCast presents:
The Voice of Change.

00:00:08.000 --> 00:00:22.000
Every movement starts with a single voice.
Today, we're listening to three voices
that have sparked significant change in their communities.

00:00:22.000 --> 00:00:45.000
MARIA RODRIGUEZ: I grew up in a neighborhood
where the air quality was so poor
that children regularly missed school
due to respiratory issues.

00:00:45.000 --> 00:01:02.000
That's when I realized that environmental justice
isn't just about saving the planet—
it's about saving lives.

00:01:02.000 --> 00:01:28.000
JAMES CHEN: Access to quality education
should never depend on your zip code.
When I started teaching, I saw firsthand
how systemic inequalities created barriers for talented students.

00:01:28.000 --> 00:01:40.000
NARRATOR: James's work with the Education Equity Initiative
has helped secure funding for under-resourced schools
across five states.

00:01:40.000 --> 00:02:00.000
AISHA WILLIAMS: The power of community organizing
lies in bringing people together
around shared values and goals.

00:02:00.000 --> 00:02:18.000
When we mobilize collectively,
we can achieve what seems impossible individually.
These stories remind us that each of us
has the power to make a difference.
